       <!-- Our Research Section -->
       <section class="bg-white py-20" id="research">
           <div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center">
               <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-12">Our Research</h2>
               <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                   <!-- Research Project 1 -->
                   <div class="bg-gray-100 p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-shadow transform hover:-translate-y-2 duration-300">
                       <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary mb-4">Past Research: Safety and Effectiveness of Cat Laser Toy</h3>
                       <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
                           In this crossover observer-blinded research study of 16 cats, exercise and stress responses were compared between a laser toy and a feather wand.
                           <span id="project1-full" class="hidden">Cats played with each toy for 10 minutes in a controlled setting, with exercise measured by distance travelled and stress assessed using the Cat Stress Score. The laser toy tended to promote more activity than the feather wand, though not significantly (p>0.166), and did not change stress scores, whereas the feather wand increased stress (p<0.048). The laser toy appears effective for increasing exercise while causing less behavioural stress than a standard toy.</span>
                       </p>
                       <button class="read-more-btn inline-block bg-secondary text-white font-semibold py-2 px-6 rounded-full hover:bg-primary transition-colors" data-target="project1-full">
                           Read More
                       </button>
                   </div>
                   <!-- Research Project 2 -->
                   <div class="bg-gray-100 p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-shadow transform hover:-translate-y-2 duration-300">
                       <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary mb-4">Past Research: Knee Osteoarthritis Treatment Effectiveness</h3>
                       <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
                           This research study is a retrospective chart review of 270 patients with knee osteoarthritis treated over 3 years in a community sports medicine clinic alongside comprehensive OA care.
                           <span id="project2-full" class="hidden">It evaluated viscosupplementation and platelet-rich plasma (PRP) injections for pain relief, functional improvement, and patient satisfaction. Viscosupplementation reduced pain by 59.8% with 79.1% satisfaction; PRP reduced pain by 53.7%, improved function by 38.7%, and achieved 78.8% satisfaction. Outcomes were better in mild-moderate OA. Both treatments were effective within a comprehensive family medicine care model.</span>
                       </p>
                       <button class="read-more-btn inline-block bg-secondary text-white font-semibold py-2 px-6 rounded-full hover:bg-primary transition-colors" data-target="project2-full">
                           Read More
                       </button>
                   </div>
                   <!-- Research Project 3 -->
                   <div class="bg-gray-100 p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-shadow transform hover:-translate-y-2 duration-300">
                       <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary mb-4">Current Research: Arthrosamid Knee Osteoarthritis Treatment Comparison</h3>
                       <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
                           This current research focuses on Arthrosamid (AS), a permanent injectable hydrogel (2.5% cross-linked polyacrylamide, 97.5% water) recently approved in Canada for knee osteoarthritis.
                           <span id="project3-full" class="hidden">AS is non-biodegradable, integrates into the synovial membrane, may act as an IL-1 receptor agonist, and has shown non-inferiority‚Äîand in some subgroups, superiority‚Äîto hyaluronic acid (HA), with potential efficacy lasting at least 5 years. It has a strong safety record from two decades of use in other conditions. This study will be the first triple-blinded randomized trial comparing AS to HA and placebo to guide clinical decision-making.</span>
                       </p>
                       <button class="read-more-btn inline-block bg-secondary text-white font-semibold py-2 px-6 rounded-full hover:bg-primary transition-colors" data-target="project3-full">
                           Read More
                       </button>
                   </div>
               </div>
           </div>
       </section>


